# 1. Introduction

This document describes the complete design, implementation, deployment, debugging, testing, and final architecture of the **Study Abroad Finder**, an AI-powered application built using **Google Agent Development Kit (Google ADK)** and multiple **Model Context Protocol (MCP)** servers.

The project was designed as a production-oriented demonstration of how a Large Language Model (LLM) can orchestrate multiple external tools to solve a complex user request.

Unlike traditional chatbots, this application does not rely solely on the language model's internal knowledge. Instead, it augments the model with specialized MCP servers, each responsible for a specific domain of expertise.

The application demonstrates how multiple tools can collaborate within a single AI agent to deliver comprehensive, structured, and up-to-date responses.

---

# 2. Project Vision

The objective of this project is to demonstrate a production-ready implementation of an AI agent capable of assisting students in planning their higher education abroad.

Instead of building a single-purpose chatbot, the project aims to showcase a modular AI architecture where individual services contribute different capabilities through MCP servers.

The long-term vision is to create an extensible AI platform where additional MCP servers can be added without redesigning the core application.

Examples include:

- University search
- Scholarship search
- Visa guidance
- Cost of living estimation
- Weather information
- Nearby attractions
- Route planning
- Accommodation search
- Flight information
- Local transportation
- Currency exchange
- Insurance providers

The Study Abroad Finder serves as a reference implementation for this architecture.

