# 7. Challenges Encountered

During development, several engineering challenges were identified.

These included:

- Python package dependency issues
- Gunicorn deployment configuration
- Google API key management
- Google Maps authentication
- Gemini model deprecation
- GitHub secret protection
- Render runtime configuration
- Docker containerization
- Filesystem MCP compatibility
- Multi-tool orchestration reliability
- Tool routing behavior within Google ADK

Each challenge was investigated, understood, documented, and resolved where possible.

The complete debugging journey is documented in later sections of this report.

---

# 8. Final Outcome

The final system demonstrates that Google ADK can successfully orchestrate multiple MCP servers within a single AI agent while being deployed as a cloud-native Docker application.

The project also highlights an important architectural insight:

> Building reliable AI systems is not only about selecting a powerful language model. It is equally about designing robust tool orchestration, deployment environments, and execution workflows.

The application serves as a strong proof of concept for enterprise-grade AI systems built using Google ADK and the Model Context Protocol.

